name: ReportFilter
description: Contains information about a report filter, including column, operator, and value.

getcolumn().name: getColumn
getcolumn().description: Returns the unique API name for the field that’s being filtered.

getoperator().name: getOperator
getoperator().description: Returns the unique API name for the condition that is used to filter a field, such as “greater than” or “not equal to.” Filter conditions depend on the data type of the field.

getfiltertype().name: getFilterType
getfiltertype().description: Returns the type of report filter.

getvalue().name: getValue
getvalue().description: Returns the value by which a field can be filtered. For example, the field Age can be filtered by a numeric value.
